The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has alleged that the All Progressives Congress (APC) plans to wear garbs belonging to the PDP and wreak havoc across the state
Special Adviser to Edo State governor, Crusoe Osagie, in a statement yesterday said, “We have received very disturbing information about plans by the APC to wreak havoc in the state, hiding un- der the identity of the PDP by
wearing shirts and caps with PDP logo. “We have informed the rel- evant security agencies of this plot and we advise members of the public to be on the alert and report such illegal actions to the police and other agen- cies charged with the task to protect lives and properties in the state.” The governor’s aide urged “supporters of the PDP and Governor Godwin Obaseki
across the state to conduct their campaign activities in a manner that befits the image of the party’s standard bear- er, as the party is committed to a free, fair and credible elec- tion that is devoid of rancor